Features:
    - Add delegated mounts for the remaining bind mounts, by calling an
      intermediary script before `exec chroot`. Example:
      unshare --mount --pid --fork sh -c '
        # 1. Perform the bind mount privately inside the namespace
        mount --bind /path/to/external/dir /path/to/chroot/internal/dir
        # 2. Pivot into the chroot and replace the shell with your executable
        exec chroot /path/to/chroot /bin/your_executable
      '
    - [sd-boot] Closely watch https://github.com/ostreedev/ostree/pull/3359
        This will be our trampoline to support bootc in the future.
        Step 1: support sd-boot alongside grub2, start building new images with sd-boot.
        Step 2: switch to UKI.
        Step 3: add bootc support.
    - Add UKI building to kernel build (make USE flag optional).
    - Test bootc & migration to UKI.
    - Support Cloud Init (add VM tests).
    - Add more VM tests (test flatpak, test snap, test SecureBoot, etc).
